    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Engine Electrical - Removal - Main Engine
        Wiring Harness
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s03.3.19" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Main Engine Wiring Harness</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent personal injury or death, remove ground cable from negative terminal of main battery
                    before disconnecting or connecting electrical components. Always connect ground cable last.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not tug on wiring harnesses; if resistance is felt, find the problem
                    and free connectors or clips.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The electrical harness assembly does not need to be disconnected from glow plug relay, unless
                    harness or relay is being replaced. Instead, relay bolts may be removed from valve cover.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect ground (-) cable from battery.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If not removed, remove
                <hotlnk document="eges3451_63.xml" xrefid="s03.3.16.ref1">Electronic Control Module (ECM) and support
                </hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s03.3.16.ref1"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect main harness from sensors.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Note routing and attachment points of main harness for reinstallation.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove wiring harness clamps that secure wiring harness to cylinder heads and front cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully lift main harness assembly from engine.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
